  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Monday. Summer vacation officially started, and Dad announced we were doing something different this year: a full tour around the island by car.",
      "zh": "星期一。暑假正式開始，爸爸宣布今年要做點不一樣的事：開車環島旅行。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We began on the highway heading east, and within an hour, the tall buildings behind us turned into distant, impressive mountains.",
      "zh": "我們從往東的高速公路出發，不到一個小時，後方的高樓大廈就變成了遠方壯麗的山脈。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William counted every tunnel we drove through, losing count somewhere after twelve, which he insisted was still an impressive personal record.",
      "zh": "William 一路數著我們穿過的每個隧道，數到十二左右就數丟了，但他堅持這仍是個很了不起的個人紀錄。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our first stop was a quiet fishing port on the east coast, where boats rocked gently and the whole town smelled like salt and fresh fish.",
      "zh": "我們第一站停在東岸一個安靜的漁港，船隻輕輕搖晃，整個小鎮聞起來都是海水鹹味和新鮮魚貨的味道。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We watched the waves crash against the rocks for almost an hour, and even William stayed quiet, which almost never happens.",
      "zh": "我們看著海浪拍打岩石看了將近一個小時，就連 William 也難得安靜下來，這種事幾乎從沒發生過。"
    },
    {
      "en": "From the port, a narrow road climbed up toward a mountain range, ending at a peak with a view so wide it felt like seeing half the island at once.",
      "zh": "從港口出發，一條窄小的道路一路爬升，通往一座山脈，終點是一座山峰，視野遼闊到感覺一次能看見半座島。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"To the north, you can see the coastline,\" Dad said, pointing. \"To the south, mountains all the way down. East is ocean, west is where we started this morning.\"",
      "zh": "「北邊可以看到海岸線，」爸爸指著說：「南邊一路都是山，東邊是海洋，西邊就是我們今早出發的地方。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That night, we stayed in a small countryside village, where the streets were narrow and every house seemed to know every other house's business.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，我們住在一個小小的鄉村村落，街道又窄，每一戶人家似乎都對其他每一戶的事一清二楚。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Instead of a car, the locals mostly rode scooters and old motorcycles, weaving between narrow lanes like it was the most natural thing in the world.",
      "zh": "當地人大多不開車，而是騎機車或老摩托車，在狹窄的巷弄間穿梭，好像那是世界上最自然不過的事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We rented two scooters ourselves the next morning, and Mom drove one with William holding on tightly, looking both terrified and thrilled at once.",
      "zh": "隔天早上我們自己也租了兩台機車，媽媽騎其中一台，William 緊緊抓著她，看起來既害怕又興奮。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the third day, we reached a bigger southern city, where we left the car at the hotel and took the subway instead to save time.",
      "zh": "到了第三天，我們抵達南部一座比較大的城市，把車留在飯店，改搭地鐵省時間。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The subway platform was crowded, but William was fascinated by watching train after train arrive exactly on schedule.",
      "zh": "地鐵月台很擁擠，但 William 對一班接一班準時抵達的列車看得入迷。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We took a taxi from the subway exit to a night market, since Dad insisted no road trip is complete without at least one proper night market visit.",
      "zh": "我們從地鐵出口搭計程車到夜市，因為爸爸堅持環島旅行沒吃到夜市就不算完整。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On our last full day, we drove west along a quieter coastal road, stopping to buy postcards at a tiny gift shop near the entrance of an old temple.",
      "zh": "在我們最後完整的一天，我們沿著比較安靜的西岸道路開車，在一座古老廟宇的入口附近，一間小小的紀念品店買了明信片。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William wrote his own postcard to Perry, which technically makes no sense since Perry cannot read, but nobody had the heart to stop him.",
      "zh": "William 寫了一張明信片給 Perry，雖然這技術上根本說不通，因為 Perry 不會看字，但沒有人忍心阻止他。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time we finished our whole loop around the island, we had used a car, two scooters, a subway, and a taxi, in that exact order.",
      "zh": "等我們完成整個環島一圈，我們已經用過汽車、兩台機車、地鐵，還有計程車，順序剛好就是這樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia, who stayed home with Perry the entire trip, said she was glad someone finally saw the whole island instead of just talking about seeing it someday.",
      "zh": "整趟旅程都留在家陪 Perry 的 Sophia 說，她很高興終於有人真正看過了整座島，而不是一直空談「總有一天要去看看」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: an island this small still manages to hide mountains, coastlines, quiet villages, and one very impressive number of tunnels.",
      "zh": "今日心得：這麼小的一座島，居然還能藏著山脈、海岸線、安靜的村落，還有數量多到令人印象深刻的隧道。"
    }
  ],
